### C++ Program to Count Words in Text Files

The following C++ program reads a text file one line at a time and calculates the number of times a specific word appears in the file. The program uses the `getline()` function from the `std::istream` library to read each line from the text file. The `strtolower()` function is used to convert the text to lowercase, and the `find()` function is used to locate the specific word in each line. Finally, the `cout` stream is used to print the number of times the word appears in the file.

```cpp
// C++ Program to Count Words in Text Files

#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <fstream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    // Declaring Variables
    string filename;
    // Reading File into String
    cout << "Enter filename: ";
    cin >> filename;
    ifstream file(filename);
    if (!file) {
        cout << "Error opening file.";
        return EXIT_FAILURE;
    }

    // Get Current Line
    string line;
    while (getline(file, line))
    {
        // Convert Line to Lowercase
        cout << line.substr(0, line.find("."))
            cout << endl;
        cout << endl;
    }

    return EXIT_SUCCESS;
}```

